<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1183,1208]" pageId="4">Description.</emphasis>
Length from apex of rostrum to apex of elytra: 
<quantity box="[904,1045,1183,1208]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.199999999999999" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="5.199999999999999" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="4.6">4.6–5.8 mm</quantity>
; length from apex of pronotum to apex of elytra: 
<quantity box="[319,458,1220,1245]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="4.15" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4.8 mm</quantity>
; width across humeral calli: 
<quantity box="[779,916,1220,1244]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="0.8" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.7">0.7–0.9 mm</quantity>
. Habitus: 
<figureCitation box="[1029,1097,1220,1245]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" box="[199,838,1255,1280]" pageId="4">Brown red with light darker postmedian blotch on elytra.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" pageId="4">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[279,361,1292,1317]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) broader than long, punctate, base slightly concave. Temples shorter than eyes, with few squamous setae on upper part. Cephalic median groove weak or missing. Vertex, metarostrum and mesorostrum grooved. Sides of metarostrum (
<figureCitation box="[524,603,1364,1389]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) glabrous. Prorostrum shorter than head, metarostrum and mesorostrum together, its length similar in both sexes. Venter of head and metarostrum with dull longitudinal median shallow groove, almost glabrous. Venter of mesorostrum with squamous setae. Antennal scape longer than antennomeres 2–3 together; articles 2–8 much broader than long, cylindrical; articles 3–8 with one row of raised setae; articles 9– 11 strongly laterally flattened in both sexes (
<figureCitation box="[649,732,1508,1533]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" pageId="4">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[330,411,1543,1568]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) shiny, punctate, with prostrate fine setae; longitudinal median groove deeper at base, weakly connected to collar constriction. Metasternum with large punctures on sides; venter longitudinally grooved. Elytra glabrous, shiny, base straight to weakly concave, humeral calli not projecting forward; striae 3–10 strongly punctate. Femora unarmed, glabrous except few thick setae at base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" pageId="4">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[341,422,1687,1712]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) with sternites III–IV punctate (but without row of punctures at apex of sternite IV), longitudinally depressed; sternites V–VI with fine line of shallow setose punctures; sternite VII of male with several large punctures, almost smooth in female (
<figureCitation box="[736,819,1759,1784]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Tergite VIII of female strongly dentate, with apical median notch; epipleurites VIII with short spiculum; spermatheca: 
