<subSubSection box="[199,1200,1868,1893]" pageId="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" box="[199,1200,1868,1893]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1868,1893]" pageId="4">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet refers to the strongly flattened articles 9–11 of antennae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1903,1928]" pageId="4">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[323,609,1903,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Stereodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platycornis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,609,1903,1928]" italics="true" pageId="4">Stereodermus platycornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[617,709,1903,1928]" pageId="4" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[617,709,1903,1928]" pageId="4">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is easily differentiated from all other taxa of the genus: it is the sole known species with articles 9–11 of antennae flattened. Its affinities with other 
<taxonomicName box="[1113,1265,1940,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Stereodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1113,1265,1940,1965]" italics="true" pageId="4">Stereodermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear. In the key given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mantilleri" box="[365,682,1976,2001]" pageId="4" refString="Mantilleri, A. &amp; Sforzi, A. (2006) Review of the Neotropical species of the genus Stereodermus Lacordaire, 1866 (Coleoptera: Brentidae: Stereodermini). Zootaxa, 1207, 3 - 64." type="journal article" year="2006">Mantilleri &amp; Sforzi (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, it is close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sharp, 1895" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1895" box="[861,1182,1976,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Stereodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticollis">
<emphasis box="[861,1026,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="4">S. puncticollis</emphasis>
Sharp, 1895
</taxonomicName>
, known from 
<collectingRegion box="[1354,1436,1976,2001]" country="Paraguay" name="Central" pageId="4">Central</collectingRegion>
America. Smaller size, shorter parameroid lobes and, above all, flattened antennomeres, separate the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
